<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-22T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-22T12:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860d.01/9: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-22T17:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            22, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 6.57 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>868. Your 792, February 19, 4 p.m. The following telegram has been
                                sent to the Legation at Stockholm: <pb facs="0296" n="211" xml:id="pg_211"/>
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Your 100, February 15, 6 p.m. Please say to Minister Enckell
                                        that I am unable to answer his question as the matter is
                                        still under consideration but that I shall not fail to
                                        advise you as soon as a decision has been reached. Copy of
                                        this telegram has been sent to the Department.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer><signed>Lansing</signed><lb/><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>